    old "The brothers exchange looks, but don’t respond. Still, this thought seems to spark the imagination of the tribesfolk, some of who remember a “harsh winter” that fell upon them a year ago, and they’d rather be sure they can buy extra supplies in autumn, or grain in spring. On the other hand, {color=#f6d6bd}Foggy{/color} mentions that food gets especially pricy during such seasons, and that it may take all of her savings much sooner than the others expect. "
