    # game/areas/creeks04othernpcs.rpy:1246
    old "A few shocked gasps encourage you to continue. You describe the ravine and the opportunities it presents, but before you can propose any plan on how to approach it, {color=#f6d6bd}Elah{/color} is on his feet, spreading his arms, sharing his own ideas on what to do next. After a few minutes of dispute, {color=#f6d6bd}Efren{/color} calls for everyone to focus. \n\n{color=#f6d6bd}The carpenter{/color} is eager to pat you on the back. “You clear a new path for the tribe, but there’s only a few of us, and we can’t know yet how much ore we’ll find in those rocks. But sharing this news with us before you take it to the officials,” he flashes his smile first toward you, then to the rest of the tribe, “is a great price to pay for our votes of trust.” "
